You need to add an Annotations flag to your config and then add the Annotations to the container.
"annotations": {"useNvidia"}

And then run a container with tue UseNvidia annotation. Not fully sure of the syntax. @wking probably would no best.

So try:

```json
"when": {
  "annotations": {
    "^io\\.kubernetes\\.cri-o\\.ContainerType$": "^sandbox$"
  }
}
```

(looks like I need to double the backslashes in the docs).

But annotations not getting passed through doesn't explain why:

```json
"when": {
  "always": true
}
```

didn't work for you earlier.

I have tried the following two versions both of which result in the command hanging.  The third 0.1.0 style works as expected.  See pastebin for the debug log from 1.0.0 syntax:  https://pastebin.com/xkFqP9Js

    {
      "hook": {
        "path": "/usr/bin/nvidia-container-runtime-hook",
        "args": ["nvidia-container-runtime-hook", "prestart"]
      },
      "when": {
        "annotations": {
          "^io\\.kubernetes\\.cri-o\\.ContainerType$": "^sandbox$"
        }
      },
      "stages": ["prestart"]
    }

Always true version:

    {
      "hook": {
        "path": "/usr/bin/nvidia-container-runtime-hook",
        "args": ["nvidia-container-runtime-hook", "prestart"]
      },
      "when": {
        "always": true
      },
      "stages": ["prestart"]
    }

Working 0.1.0 version:

    {
       "hook": "/usr/bin/nvidia-container-runtime-hook",
       "arguments": ["prestart"],
       "annotations": ["sandbox"],
       "stage": [ "prestart" ]
    }

The reason for the hanging seemed to be the omission of the version information:

    {
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "hook": {
        "path": "/usr/bin/nvidia-container-runtime-hook",
        "args": ["nvidia-container-runtime-hook", "prestart"]
      },
      "when": {
        "always": true
      },
      "stages": ["prestart"]
    }

The command now runs but the hook does not seem to be triggered as non of the Nvidia tools are mounted.

> The reason for the hanging seemed to be the omission of the version information:

I've filed #887 to fix that in the example (and fix a few other things as well).  But with the missing `version` we should be failing to unmarshal the JSON using the 0.1.0 structure.  For example:

```console
$ cat /tmp/hook.json 
{
  "hook": {
    "path": "/bin/sh",
    "args": ["nvidia-container-runtime-hook", "prestart"],
    "env": [
      "NVIDIA_REQUIRE_CUDA=cuda>=9.1",
      "NVIDIA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=GPU-fef8089b"
    ]
  },
  "when": {
    "annotations": {
      "^com\\.example\\.department$": ".*fluid-dynamics$"
    }
  },
  "stages": ["prestart"]
}
$ git describe 
v0.6.1
$ cat test.go 
package main

import (
        "context"
        "fmt"
        "os"
        rspec "github.com/opencontainers/runtime-spec/specs-go"
        "github.com/projectatomic/libpod/pkg/hooks"
        _ "github.com/projectatomic/libpod/pkg/hooks/0.1.0"
        "github.com/sirupsen/logrus"
        "golang.org/x/text/language"
)

func die(err error) {
        fmt.Printf("%v\n", err)
        os.Exit(1)
}

func main() {
        ctx := context.Background()

        logrus.SetLevel(logrus.DebugLevel)

        lang, err := language.Parse("und-u-va-posix")
        if err != nil {
                die(err)
        }

        manager, err := hooks.New(ctx, []string{"/tmp"}, []string{}, lang)
        if err != nil {
                die(err)
        }

        config := &rspec.Spec{}
        _, err = manager.Hooks(config, map[string]string{
                "com.example.department": "fluid-dynamics",
        }, false)
        if err != nil {
                die(err)
        }

        fmt.Printf("%v\n", config)
}
$ go run test.go 
parsing hook "/tmp/hook.json": : json: cannot unmarshal object into Go struct field Hook.hook of type string
exit status 1
